The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 South Eastern Railway will run special trains to Puri and Digha to clear the winter rush. The special trains between Howrah and Puri will run on January 14, and between Shalimar and Digha on January 15, 22 and 29. The train for Puri will leave Howrah at 11.30 pm on January 14 and reach its destination the next day at 11.15 am. It will leave Puri on January 15 at 10.45 pm and reach Howrah at 9.10 am the following day.

 he trains for Digha will leave Shalimar at 1.30 pm and reach there at 5.30 pm. The departure from Digha is scheduled for 6 pm.

 Air Deccan has cancelled some flights till January 31 because of temporary closure of airfields. Among the flights cancelled are DN 555 Calcutta-Bhubaneswar, DN 556 Bhubaneswar-Calcutta, DN 577 Calcutta-Raipur and DN 578 Raipur-Calcutta. The airline said passengers who have booked tickets on the flights will be entitled to full refunds or a free rescheduling to a later date.

 An unidentified man died in an accidental fire in Salt Lake Sector V on Tuesday morning. Police said the man was warming himself by a fire when the accident occurred.

 More than 1,500 Trinamul Congress activists, including 50 women, were arrested on Tuesday while they were marching towards Lalbazar. Police intercepted the marchers on BB Ganguly Street. The protesters were released in the evening.

 The industrial trade fair in Baruipur, on the southern fringes of the city, ends on Sunday. The valedictory function will be attended by Union ministers Priya Ranjan Das Munshi and Subodh Kant Sahay, and state industries minister Nirupam Sen and Sunderbans affairs minister Kanti Ganguly. The fair, organised by the Cottage and Small Scale Industries Association, South 24-Parganas, was inaugurated by chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on January 6. 

 A man, in his early 40s, was killed after being knocked down by a private bus at the intersection of Brabourne Road and Canning Street on Tuesday morning. Police said the victim, Chandidas Banerjee, a resident of Howrah, was crossing the road when he was hit by a bus on route 55A. The driver fled with the vehicle.

 A full-size bronze statue of Swami Vivekananda will be unveiled at Central Park, in Salt Lake, on January 12. The statue has been built and installed with funds from Bidhannagar Vivekananda Smarak Samity, a voluntary organisation. The statue will be unveiled by the secretary, Ramakrishna Math and Mission.

 Former state health minister Prasanta Sur was admitted to SSKM Hospital on Monday after his blood sugar level dropped sharply. 

 The scholarship examination for Class IV students will be held from February 6 to 11. A total of 303,000 students will sit for the test, being conducted by the Primary Education Development Board.

